text.section:
As used in KRS 189.920 to 189.950, "emergency vehicle" means any vehicle used for emergency purposes by:
The Department of Kentucky State Police;
A public police department;
The Department of Corrections;
A sheriff's office;
A rescue squad;
An emergency management agency if it is a publicly owned vehicle;
An ambulance service or medical first-response provider licensed by the Kentucky Board of Emergency Medical Services, for any vehicle used to respond to emergencies or to transport a patient with a critical medical condition;
Any vehicle commandeered by a police officer;
Any vehicle with the emergency lights required under KRS 189.920 used by a paid or volunteer fireman or paid or volunteer ambulance personnel, or a paid or local emergency management director while responding to an emergency or to a location where an emergency vehicle is on emergency call;
An elected coroner granted permission to equip a publicly or privately owned motor vehicle with lights and siren pursuant to KRS 189.920; or
A deputy coroner granted permission to equip a publicly or privately owned motor vehicle with lights and siren pursuant to KRS 189.920.
